<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Adaptive_Runge=E2=80=93Kutt=
a_methods"><span id=3D"Adaptive_Runge.E2.80.93Kutta_methods"></span>Adaptiv=
e Runge=E2=80=93Kutta methods</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/=
index.php?title=3DRunge%E2%80%93Kutta_methods&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=
=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Adaptive Runge=E2=80=93Kutta methods"><span>ed=
it</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Adaptive methods are designed to produce an estimate of the local trunca=
tion error of a single Runge=E2=80=93Kutta step. This is done by having two=
 methods, one with order <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-i=
nline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D=
"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=
=3D"{\displaystyle p}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>p</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle p}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/81eac1e205430d1f40810df36a0edffdc367af36" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:1.259ex; height:2.009ex;" al=
t=3D"{\displaystyle p}"></span> and one with order <span class=3D"mwe-math-=
element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-=
math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org=
/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle p-1}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>p</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle p-1}</annotat=
ion>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f356ae51988add41a7da343e6b6d48fa968da162" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:5.262ex; height:2.509ex;" al=
t=3D"{\displaystyle p-1}"></span>. These methods are interwoven, i.e., they=
 have common intermediate steps. Thanks to this, estimating the error has l=
ittle or negligible computational cost compared to a step with the higher-o=
rder method.
</p><p>During the integration, the step size is adapted such that the estim=
ated error stays below a user-defined threshold: If the error is too high, =
a step is repeated with a lower step size; if the error is much smaller, th=
e step size is increased to save time. This results in an (almost), optimal=
 step size, which saves computation time. Moreover, the user does not have =
to spend time on finding an appropriate step size.
</p><p>The lower-order step is given by
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e y_{n+1}^{*}=3Dy_{n}+h\sum _{i=3D1}^{s}b_{i}^{*}k_{i},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msubsup>
          <mi>y</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=97<!-- =E2=88=97 --></mo>
          </mrow>
        </msubsup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>y</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>h</mi>
        <munderover>
          <mo>=E2=88=91<!-- =E2=88=91 --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>s</mi>
          </mrow>
