<p>Other adaptive Runge=E2=80=93Kutta methods are the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bogacki%E2%80%93Shampine_method" title=3D"Bogacki=E2=80=
=93Shampine method">Bogacki=E2=80=93Shampine method</a> (orders 3 and 2), t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cash%E2%80%93Karp_method" title=
=3D"Cash=E2=80=93Karp method">Cash=E2=80=93Karp method</a> and the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dormand%E2%80%93Prince_method" title=3D"D=
ormand=E2=80=93Prince method">Dormand=E2=80=93Prince method</a> (both with =
orders 5 and 4).
</p>
