nd implicit methods">explicit methods</a>. Explicit Runge=E2=80=93Kutta met=
hods are generally unsuitable for the solution of <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Stiff_equation" title=3D"Stiff equation">stiff equations</a=
> because their region of absolute stability is small; in particular, it is=
 bounded.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-26" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Runge%E2%80%93Kutta_methods#cite_note-26"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
This issue is especially important in the solution of <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numerical_partial_differential_equations" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"Numerical partial differential equations">partial differe=
ntial equations</a>.
