<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Stability">Stability</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DRunge%E2%80%93Kutt=
a_methods&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Stabil=
ity"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>The advantage of implicit Runge=E2=80=93Kutta methods over explicit ones=
 is their greater stability, especially when applied to <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stiff_equation" title=3D"Stiff equation">stiff equati=
ons</a>. Consider the linear test equation <span class=3D"mwe-math-element =
mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mat=
hml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Ma=
th/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle y'=3D\lambda y}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
